      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;foreword&#34;&gt;Foreword&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;GitHub has a very nice notification system, very similar to a plain old email inbox. You receive a notification which&#xA;remains &lt;em&gt;unread&lt;/em&gt; until you actually read it; then it&amp;rsquo;s archived and removed from your &lt;em&gt;inbox&lt;/em&gt;, which it happens could remain empty:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;figure&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;    &lt;picture&#xA;      class=&#34;mx-auto my-0 rounded-md&#34;&#xA;      &#xA;    &gt;&#xA;      &#xA;      &#xA;      &#xA;      &#xA;        &lt;source&#xA;          &#xA;            srcset=&#34;https://dev.pippi.im/writing/build-github-like-notifications-with-django-messages-and-angular-js/github_notifications_hu_41c587e860b771e0.webp 330w,https://dev.pippi.im/writing/build-github-like-notifications-with-django-messages-and-angular-js/github_notifications_hu_8ee305e177ee3ccc.webp 660w&#xA;            &#xA;              &#xA;                ,https://dev.pippi.im/writing/build-github-like-notifications-with-django-messages-and-angular-js/github_notifications_hu_8019ab29f3cae25b.webp 1023w&#xA;              &#xA;            &#xA;            &#xA;              &#xA;                ,https://dev.pippi.im/writing/build-github-like-notifications-with-django-messages-and-angular-js/github_notifications_hu_8019ab29f3cae25b.webp 1023w&#xA;              &#xA;            &#34;&#xA;          &#xA;          sizes=&#34;100vw&#34;&#xA;          type=&#34;image/webp&#34;&#xA;        /&gt;&#xA;      &#xA;      &lt;img&#xA;        width=&#34;1023&#34;&#xA;        height=&#34;546&#34;&#xA;        class=&#34;mx-auto my-0 rounded-md&#34;&#xA;        alt=&#34;github inbox&#34;&#xA;        loading=&#34;lazy&#34; decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xA;        &#xA;          src=&#34;https://dev.pippi.im/writing/build-github-like-notifications-with-django-messages-and-angular-js/github_notifications_hu_7b191d354fa85b37.png&#34; srcset=&#34;https://dev.pippi.im/writing/build-github-like-notifications-with-django-messages-and-angular-js/github_notifications_hu_2230e08972812bc0.png 330w,https://dev.pippi.im/writing/build-github-like-notifications-with-django-messages-and-angular-js/github_notifications_hu_7b191d354fa85b37.png 660w&#xA;          &#xA;            ,https://dev.pippi.im/writing/build-github-like-notifications-with-django-messages-and-angular-js/github_notifications.png 1023w&#xA;          &#xA;          &#xA;            ,https://dev.pippi.im/writing/build-github-like-notifications-with-django-messages-and-angular-js/github_notifications.png 1023w&#xA;          &#34;&#xA;          sizes=&#34;100vw&#34;&#xA;        &#xA;      /&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/picture&gt;&#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;For those who don&amp;rsquo;t know, Django ships a library for displaying &amp;ldquo;one-time&amp;rdquo; messages to the users, it&amp;rsquo;s called &lt;em&gt;Message&#xA;Framework&lt;/em&gt; and you can find it in the &lt;code&gt;contrib&lt;/code&gt; package. Messages are &lt;em&gt;produced&lt;/em&gt; during users&amp;rsquo; activity and delivered&#xA;subsequently; in the meantime, they are stored in cookies or sessions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
